OL,3,CFormer rail worker converts part of
OL,4,Chis home into library
OL,6,FFor fifty years Paul Salveson has been
OL,7,Fcollecting books about trains - how
OL,8,Fthey work, what they do, and the ways
OL,9,Fin which they've contributed to social
OL,10,Fand cultural history.
OL,12,FNow, it's a passion, and a collection
OL,13,Fhe's able to share with the world. His
OL,14,Fbooks are the centrepiece of a new
OL,15,Flibrary he's opened in his own home,
OL,16,Fat Kents Bank Station near Grange-over-
OL,17,FSands. It could be the only one of its
OL,18,Fkind in the UK.
