OL,3,CFormer rail worker converts part of
OL,4,Chis home into library
OL,6,FA childhood love for the railways
OL,7,Fsparked a career on the tracks - Paul
OL,8,Fexplained his first job was as a train
OL,9,Fguard, and throughout his career he
OL,10,Fwas keen to share his passion, and
OL,11,Fknowledge, with both colleagues and
OL,12,Fpassengers.
OL,14,F"The history of railways," he
OL,15,Fexplained, is "not just the engines,
OL,16,Fas much as we all love steam, but also
OL,17,Fthe social history, the contribution
OL,18,Fthat railways have made to the world
OL,19,Fthat we're in today."
