OL,3,CFormer rail worker converts part of
OL,4,Chis home into library
OL,6,FIt's not just the books that are the
OL,7,Fattraction either. The library is
OL,8,Fhoused in Paul's home - a house was
OL,9,Ffirst opened in 1865 and was extended
OL,10,Fin 1890 for the former station master
OL,11,Fof the tiny Kents Bank Station near
OL,12,FGrange, on the Furness Line.
OL,14,F"I think there was pressure locally to
OL,15,Fbuild a proper station," Paul said.
OL,17,F"In the end, the Furness Railway
OL,18,Fdecided to build the proper station
OL,19,Fbuilding, which is this, and so the
OL,20,Fstation master and his family lived
OL,21,Fhere."
